column6: company_profile

Maruhan operates entertainment facilities. It operates facilities, such as pachinko parlors, bowling alleys, golf driving ranges, amusement facilities, cinemas, and other leisure-related business. The company was founded in 1957 and is based in Kyoto, Japan.

TOA Paint, together with its subsidiaries and joint ventures, develops and produces paints for various applications. It provides architectural coatings; protective coatings; marine system coatings; wood coatings for furniture, kitchenware, flooring, and toys applications; and construction chemicals, including waterproofing products, joint sealants, elastic bonding, and concrete repair and protection products. TOA Paint was founded in 1972 and is based in Bangkok, Thailand.

Bollore operates as a holding company. It offers transportation, logistics, communications, and electricity and storage solutions. Additionally, it manages a portfolio withing the communication and agricultural sector, which includes oil palm and rubber trees plantations, video game console suppliers, and manufacturers of steel tubes. It was founded in 1822 and is based in Puteaux, France.

column6: VTSIX Group is a pharmaceutical company produces a wide range of oral pharmaceuticals, including tablets, capsules and syrups. The firm is based in India.

International Workplace Group (IWG), together with its subsidiaries, provides office outsourcing services. IWG offers its services to property owners and investors, franchisees, brokers, and customers under the Regus, Regus Express, Spaces, Signature, and Open Office brands. Effective October 14, 2008, Regus Group plc became Regus plc. Regus plc was created as a holding company for Regus Group plc, to establish the company's headquarters in Luxembourg, relocating from the UK. The company was formerly known as Regus before rebranding to IWG in December 2016. In December 2016, the company relocated its head office from Luxembourg to Switzerland. IWG was established in 1989 and is based in Zug, Switzerland.

Mobile World Investment Corporation engages in trading, repair, and maintenance of phones in Vietnam. It offers phones, information technology equipment, cameras, digital equipment, electronic equipment, household appliances, and related accessories. The company was founded in 2004 and is headquartered in Ho Chi Minh, Vietnam.

DaChan Greatwall Group, founded in Taiwan in 1958, is the largest agribusiness and animal husbandry company in Taiwan, and is also one of the top two food processing companies in Taiwan and one of the top three meat production companies in mainland China. The group has direct investments in mainland China, Taiwan, the Philippines, Vietnam, Malaysia and Indonesia, with over twenty operations in mainland China.In mainland China, Taiwan and other Asian markets, DaChan Greatwall Group is one of the leaders in food service, flour milling, animal feed, meat production and edible oils.

Rouse is a leading global IP consultancy that provides the full range of Intellectual Property services. Its services include patent and trademark protection and management, commercialisation and global enforcement, and anti-counterfeiting programmes. Founded in 1990, it is headquartered in London, UK.
column36: Luke Minford, chief executive officer, states: "The ASEAN region represents a huge growth opportunity for us and our clients. Cambodia is one of the fastest growing economies in Asia and we know the demand for our services in the country is high  both from our existing client base, and from new and prospective clients."

column6: AP Moller - Maersk is a shipping firm. It is active in ocean and inland freight transportation and associated services, such as supply chain management and port operation. The company was established in 1904 and is headquartered in Copenhagen, Denmark.

D.B. Group provides air, sea, and road freight forwarding and logistics services in Italy and internationally. D.B. Group was formerly known as De Bortoli Trasporti and changed its name to D.B. Group in 2007. The company was founded in 1950 and is based in Montebelluna, Italy.
Times Cargo Logistic is a global logistics services provider. It was founded in 2010 and is based in Ho Chi Minh, Vietnam.
Histar International is a manufacturer of stationary products. It was founded in 2014 and is based in Qingdao, China

East-West is a multinational vegetable seed producer with a leading market position in all major south-east and south Asian vegetable seed markets. It produces, develops and sells tropical hybrid vegetable seeds under the brand logo 'Red Arrow'. Started in 1982 in the Philippines, East-West has today operations in all major south-east and south Asian vegetable seed markets. The roots then and now remain unchanged; innovative breeding towards improved hybrid varieties that challenge existing market situations. The company is headquartered in Thailand.

Nihon Seimitsu Co., Ltd. manufactures and sells wristwatch bands, eyeglass frames, and other products in Japan. The company offers carbide ceramic and pure titanium wristwatch, metal, and urethane bands, as well as bezels. It also provides fishing tackles, static electricity eliminators, and electronic locks, as well as ion plating services. The company was founded in 1978 and is headquartered in Kawaguchi, Japan.

Blackwell Global offers brokerage solutions for private and institutional clients, along with other investments products. Blackwell Global is a straight-through-processing brokerage providing superior liquidity and price feeds from top international banks, 24-hour technical support, market research tools, educational materials, professional partnership programmes, and a fully-integrated Blackwell Trader platform to its clients. Founded in 2010, the company is headquartered in Auckland, New Zealand.

Rahim & Co Chartered Surveyors operates as a real estate and property consultancy company in Malaysia. It provides property valuation, research and advisory, property sales and leasing, property and facilities management, marketing, project management, auctioneering, and investment consultancy services. Rahim & Co Chartered Surveyors was founded in 1976 and is based in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.
Deutsche Post provides logistics and communications services. The company was founded in 1995 and is based in Bonn, Germany.

Tokio Marine Holdings, Inc., through its subsidiaries, engages in non-life insurance and life insurance businesses. It offers property and casualty, life, and reinsurance products. The company also provides various financial services, risk consulting, individual financial consulting services and business process outsourcing services. Additionally, it offers nursing care services under the Hyldemoer and Hutte brands. The company was formerly known as Millea Holdings and changed its name in 2008. Tokio Marine Holdings was founded in 2002 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.

Axiata Group, an investment holding company, provides various telecommunication and network transmission related services. The company offers mobile telecommunication, passive infrastructure leasing, interconnect, leased, pay television transmission, and other data services; and telecommunication network capacity, infrastructure, and services. The company was formerly known as TM International and changed its name to Axiata Group in March 2009. Axiata Group was incorporated in 1992 and is headquartered in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.

Diethelm Keller Holding, along with its subsidiaries, engages in marketing, brand management, logistics and travel businesses. The company provides sourcing, marketing, sales, distribution and aftersales services. It also offers marketing, brand building and distribution services for medium-sized enterprises. Diethelm Keller Holding was founded in 2000 as a result of a merger between Diethelm and Edward Keller. The company is headquartered in Zurich, Switzerland.
Alfred Karcher develops cleaning equipment, including carpet sweepers and pressure washers. Alfred Karcher was founded in 1935 and is based in Winnenden, Germany.
column27: Cosmetics, perfume, personal care & household products

column6: Global Green Growth Institute was established to create an international platform for evidence-based learning and policy innovation that helps to illuminate practical opportunities for country-led and industry-led progress on the twin imperatives of economic development and environmental sustainability. Through its developing country, industry and research activities, it seeks to serve as a bridge between developed and developing countries, the public and private sectors, and practitioners and scholars, respectively. The company was established in 2010 and is based in Seoul, South Korea.
Russia-based Grand Capital is a forex broker. The company was founded in 2006 and is based in Moscow, Russia.

Bangkok Dusit Medical Services engages in the hospital business in Thailand and internationally. The company owns and manages six hospital groups, including Bangkok Hospital Group, Samitivej Group, BNH Hospital, Phyathai Hospital Group, Paolo Memorial Hospital Group, and the Royal Hospital Group. It offers medical services in the areas of allergy and asthma, anesthesiology, anti-ageing, sports and exercise medicine, aviation medicine, bone and joint, dental, trauma and emergency, mental health rehabilitation and recovery, neurology, and spine. It was founded in 1969 and is based in Bangkok, Thailand.
column27: Outpatient care centres & medical & diagnostic laboratories

column6: Mobile World Investment Corporation engages in trading, repair, and maintenance of phones in Vietnam. It offers phones, information technology equipment, cameras, digital equipment, electronic equipment, household appliances, and related accessories. The company was founded in 2004 and is headquartered in Ho Chi Minh, Vietnam.

Taisun engages in the manufacture of disposable baby diapers, adult incontinent products and female sanitary products. The company markets its products under the brand UniDry, UniDry Super, Summed, Maeva, YoYo and Unifresh. It is based in Ho Chi Minh, Vietnam.

AIA Group Limited provides various products and services for insurance, protection, savings, investment, and retirement needs of individuals and businesses. It offers life, pensions, and accident and health insurance products; savings and investment products; wealth management solutions; and employee benefits, credit insurance, and retirement services. The company distributes its products and services through direct marketing, agents, and bancassurance relationships primarily in Hong Kong, Thailand, Singapore, Malaysia, China, Korea, the Philippines, Indonesia, Vietnam, India, Australia, New Zealand, and Taiwan. American International Assurance was founded in 1919 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong.
column36: "We believe that Cambodia holds great potential as a life insurance market with its young and growing population, solid economic growth, expanding middle class and very low penetration rate of private life coverage." - Ng Keng Hooi, chief executive officer.

column6: Vicplas International, an investment holding company, researches, designs, develops, manufactures, and assembles medical devices. It operates through two segments, pipes and pipe fittings, and medical devices. Vicplas International was founded in 1993 and is based in Singapore.
column27: Plastic pipes, pipe fitting & unlaminated profile shapes

column6: The Central Group of Companies engages in retailing, hotels and resorts, property, wholesaling, manufacturing and food franchise operations. Its activities include operating department stores, importing and distributing apparel, textiles, household electrical appliances, camera and music instruments, cosmetics and electric appliances. The company also engages in the development of hotels, department stores, shopping centres, condominiums and office buildings. The Central Group was founded in 1947 and is based in Bangkok, Thailand.
Heineken Holding supervises the management of the Heineken group. The company was established in 1952 and is based in Amsterdam, the Netherlands.

SVI provides electronic manufacturing services. The company operates in two segments, industrial control system and niche products. The company serves industrial, automotive and transportation, medical, communications and networks, audio/video, and photonics and lighting markets. SVI was established in 1985 and is headquartered in Pathumthani, Thailand.

Siam Cement engages in chemicals, paper, cement, building materials, distribution, and investment businesses in Thailand and internationally. The company also has a joint venture with Sekisui Chemical to manufacture modular houses. The company is headquartered in Bangkok, Thailand, and was founded in 1913.

column5: Bank for Foreign Trade of Vietnam (Vietcombank)
column6: Vietcombank provides banking products and services for individuals, corporates, and financial institutions in Vietnam and internationally. The company accepts personal and savings accounts; and business accounts, such as current accounts, and time and special deposit products. Its loan products comprise personal loans; and short-term lending, working capital financing, project finance, and trade finance products. Vietcombank was founded in 1963 and is headquartered in Hanoi, Vietnam.

Mizuho Financial Group provides various financial services through its subsidiaries. The group's services include general banking, securities brokerage, trust banking, and assets management. Mizuho Financial Group was founded in 2003 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
column36: Cambodia occupies a key area along the 'Southern Economic Corridor', which connects Thailand and Vietnam, the two largest economies in the fast-growing Greater Mekong sub-region. Since the restoration of the monarchy in 1993, Cambodia has enjoyed political stability and a high level of GDP growth.

column6: AnyMind Group, formerly known as AdAsia Holdings, is an advertising company. It offers digital marketing platform, digital strategy, video production/advertising, advanced TV advertising, mobile marketing, social media marketing, influencer marketing, cloud CRM, O2O, omni channel marketing, global marketing and marketing automation services. It was founded in 2016 and is based in Singapore.
column36: "In the past year there has been a rise in mobile device and social media usage, along with mobile broadband penetration in Cambodia. Our offerings including Parallax, CastingAsia and other mobile solutions, will allow us to enable marketers to capture users in a fast-emerging market." - Kosuke Sogo, chief executive officer.

column6: The Zuellig Group operates healthcare, agribusiness, and agricultural and materials handling equipment businesses in the Asia-Pacific region. It provides inventory management, warehousing, distribution, customer order management, clinical trial logistics, patient-based solutions, and retail management assistance to doctors, hospitals, pharmacies, and clinics; offers pharmaceutical wholesaling and retail management solutions for community pharmacies; provides retail pharmacy software solutions; offers pharmaceutical distribution services to public and private hospitals; and provides clinical trials logistics support and speciality contract logistics services for healthcare manufacturers. The company was founded in 1912 and is based in Wan Chai, Hong Kong.

It provides inventory management, warehousing, distribution, customer order management, clinical trial logistics, patient-based solutions, and retail management assistance to doctors, hospitals, pharmacies, and clinics; offers pharmaceutical wholesaling and retail management solutions for community pharmacies; provides retail pharmacy software solutions; offers pharmaceutical distribution services to public and private hospitals; and provides clinical trials logistics support and speciality contract logistics services for healthcare manufacturers. The company was founded in 1912 and is based in Wan Chai, Hong Kong.
column36: "Its location in the city centre ensures easy access to our clients and customers." - Jean-Gaetan Guillemaud, country manager, Zuellig Pharma (Cambodia).

column6: Tune Group, through its subsidiaries, engages in airline, hotel, telecommunication, financial services, sports and media and creative industries primarily in Malaysia. The company operates an airline carrier that provides passenger transportation services to various destinations worldwide from hubs located in Malaysia, Thailand and Indonesia, operates a chain of hotels in Malaysia, Indonesia, Thailand, the Philippines and the UK and operates a mobile virtual network that provides mobile calling and SMS services in Malaysia. Tune Group was founded in 2001 and is based in Petaling Jaya, Malaysia.

China Ocean Fishing Holdings, an investment holding company, engages in supply chain management and money lending businesses in China. The company provides supply chain management services, such as planning and implementing of an integrated solution for the flow of business, logistic, information, and funds to small and medium sized enterprises in various industries. It also offers money lending services to individuals and corporations. In addition, the company trades in wood, metal, and electronic products, as well as seafood; and provides ship building, as well as administration services. China Ocean Fishing Holdings was incorporated in 2001 and is based in Wan Chai, Hong Kong.
